text: Lappatubby Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Lappatubby is a name derived from a Native American language (Choctaw or Chickasaw) purported to mean "buck killer". A variant name is "Lappatuppy Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Pontotoc County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Union County, Mississippi
title: Lappatubby Creek
